cnuphys.tinyMS.message
Class Header

java.lang.Object
  cnuphys.tinyMS.message.Header

public class Header
extends java.lang.Object

The header for a message. The header consists of 1: (int) the magic word TinyMessageServer.MAGIC_WORD=0xCEBAF 2: (int) id of the source of the message (0 if server) 3: (int) id of the destination of the message (0 if server) 4: (short) value of a MessageType enum 5: (short) a tag for further differentiation 6: (short) value of the DataType enum 7: (int) the length of the data array in the body (might be 0) 8: (short) user1 for application specific use 9: (short) user2 for application specific use

Author:
heddle

public boolean isSwap()
If true, the bytes were swapped when creating this header from a read of a DataInputStream.

Returns:
true if the header required a swap to match the magic word. If so, the payload will require swapping too.

getDataLength
